(222, '220', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'What would you like to see in our Migration Museum', NULL, 'I’d like to see an exhibition about people who have partners from families who came here to the UK… and on how that changed their lives.', NULL, '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KW16hfoeNAPTEhraSwW-X4T4kcqPyKLk/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(223, '221', NULL, NULL, '1970s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'China;Hong Kong;Malaysia', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My mum came from Malaysia and my dad from Hong Kong. Both migrated in the 70s and have lived in the UK longer than their native countries.', 'China;Family;Hong Kong;Malaysia', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_zx-05NSid9pCeekqn5IAIO6QW0sp6rK/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(224, '222', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Child Migration', 'Economic', 'Love', 'Kenya', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I’m from Kenya! Born there and lived there till I was 8 years old. My mum got a job in London for 2 years contract, she then decided to bring my brother and I, my dad brought us to her and then her contract was made permanent and since then we have always lived here and visited Kenya many many times!', 'Commerce;Family;Kenya;Work', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/16t8eX-8EmwPiZVhlfkfoZXeLFIVgWwo2/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(225, '223', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Fiji', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I came from Fiji and stayed in England ever since. I came when Fuji was a British Crown colony and was all smooth and plain sailing. Happy to be in England.', 'Empire;Fiji', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/18J6QMh6mMRjk5Ml2X_LfPH-OgAUdDbYz/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 1, 0),
(226, '224', NULL, NULL, '1940s', 'Image', NULL, 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'Both of my grandparents got evacuated to Cornwall, Devon in the 1940s due to World War 2. This is important.', 'Family;Genocide;Third Person;War', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1GzmxwV9-ZsnaaQi6a6gPcILotXuaUw1J/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(228, '226', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'What would you like to see in our Migration Museum', NULL, 'Have any Asian migrated to Great Britain? Especially on the wall of pictures of different class/ background/ race. I feel like Asian migrants were underrepresented. If there were more inclusion of Asian migrants (if there were a lot) then I think the museum would be more complete than it is.', NULL, '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1HfdW7VSsVxqCLDPQXDxFxJO4KNZ9sl1K/view?usp=sharing', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(229, '227', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, 'Education', NULL, NULL, 'Ghana;Italy', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I was born in Italy and then moved to Ghana with my brother. Then I returned to Italy when I was 3 and went to school. Then I moved to England for education.', 'Education;Family;Ghana;Italy', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(230, '228', NULL, NULL, '1970s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sri Lanka', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My parents migrated to London (1979 and 1999) to escape conflict in Sri Lanka.', 'Family;Sri Lanka;Third Person;War', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(231, '229', 'Salome', NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USA', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I kind of migrated from England to America but back to England because my parents weren’t sure where to live still, but moved back again.', 'Family;USA', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(232, '230', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Ireland', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My parents came to England from Ireland to work. I am one of 6 children and I have more than 50 first cousins until I was 13, I had never been on Holiday to anywhere other than home to Ireland.', 'Family;Ireland;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(233, '231', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My grandmother went from Bristol to Lincolnshire, my grandfather from London to Scarborough to Clacton (and several places in between), my mother from Lincolnshire to Cambridge, my father from Scarborough to Cambridge, I went from Cambridge to London.', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'removed for education ', 0, 0),
(234, '232', NULL, 'heatherlundie@aol.com', '1950s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'India', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'We-my dad,mum, and my sister and I came back to the UK on SS Arcadia on the 26th April 1955 from India (Calcutta). We came for a better life and work.', 'Family;India;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 16),
(235, '233', NULL, NULL, '1990s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jamaica', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My parents moved here from Jamaica in the 90’s. Both from farming backgrounds and now have two kids and are graduating from uni.', 'Education;Family;Jamaica;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(236, '234', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Education', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My mum moved here for a better education to be prepared for me and my sister.', 'Education;Family;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(237, '235', NULL, NULL, '1960s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Barbados', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandmother migrated to the UK from Barbados in 1964, she met the love of her life and married in 1991, she became an English teacher and settled in Charlton.', 'Barbados;Family;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(238, '236', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Child Migration', NULL, NULL, 'Guyana', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'Both of my parents migrated here from Guyana. Myself and my brothers were born here but grew up in Guyana. I came back here at 17 and had a bit of culture shock. Now I feel like home is here in England.', 'Alienation;Culture;Family;Guyana;', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'removed for education ', 0, 0),
(239, '237', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'What would you like to see in our Migration Museum', NULL, 'I’d like to see Boris Johnson, Priti Patel and Kevin Foster here-explaining their rationale for #Jamaica50.', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(240, '238', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Pakistan', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My mum migrated to the UK from Pakistan after she got married and my sister was born a year later after my mum’s marriage.', 'Family;Pakistan;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(241, '239', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Syria', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My father’s parents came from Aleppo to Manchester(Via Cairo in my grandfather’s case- the cotton trade). I am so lucky to have been born in Manchester not Aleppo but I know too little of my heritage.', 'Egypt;Pride;Syria;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1),
(242, '240', NULL, NULL, '1950s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Italy', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, '¾ of my grandparents migrated from Italy in the 50/60s. I’m grateful that they did this, working extremely hard when they got here in hope for more opportunities for their future family.', 'Family;Italy;Pride;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(243, '241', NULL, NULL, '1990s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Sri Lanka', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'Our parents fled from the Sri Lankan civil war in 1996. They could not speak English and had very little money. They worked hard and tried to assimilate in a new culture. Without them we would be nothing.', 'Assimilation;Culture;Family;Genocide;Language;Third Person;War;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(244, '242', NULL, NULL, '1960s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Guyana', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My parents came from Guyana in the early 1960s. Not an easy life for them but they wanted a self secure life for the family. They missed the Guyanese life and sun.', 'Family;Guyana;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(245, '243', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jamaica', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I have had family members migrate here from Jamaica and they have migrated back to Jamaica and they now occasionally return to visit children and grandchildren', 'Family;Jamaica;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'removed for education ', 1, 0),
(246, '244', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Love', NULL, NULL, 'Jamaica', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I followed ‘love’ and ended up here. As a result, all my children were born here. I’m still in ‘love’. I am Jamaican.', 'Family;Jamaica', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(247, '245', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Poland', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My parents migrated from Poland to the UK to get a job and get money. Now my dad works as a builder for my uncle.', 'Family;Poland;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0),
(248, '246', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I migrated here looking for a better future for myself and my family. Although I’m far away from them, I know I will be the piece of our puzzle that will make the difference. I’m grateful to be here.', 'Family;Pride', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(249, '247', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'What would you like to see in our Migration Museum', NULL, 'The future, I really like the idea of 2020 predictions. The influence of migration on sport, music, and art. A map showing the timeline of when waves of people arrived.', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(250, '248', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USA', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I grew up in Texas, USA and always felt out of place. I wanted to move abroad though I didn’t know where. My husband got a job in London and I was so happy to move! I feel safer here and like I fit in. Also found out later from a DNA test that I’m 50% British. Destiny!', 'Assimilation;Ethnicity;Family;USA;Work', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 0),
(251, '249', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Education', NULL, NULL, 'France;Ireland;Russia;South Africa', 'Disc', 'I migrated here', NULL, 'I moved to London from Dublin, Ireland, where I spent 10 years. I moved to Dublim from South Africa. I moved to South Africa from France. I moved to France from Russia to go to uni. I’m originally from Moscow. And the UK because the fifth country for me.', 'Education;France;Ireland;Russia;South Africa', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(252, '250', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Pakistan', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My great-grandparents and my grandparents also my dad from Pakistan, also my uncle and aunt. I have had 3 generations migrate. Soon, my cousin is coming too.', 'Family;Pakistan;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'removed for education ', 0, 0),
(253, '251', 'Danielle Lawrence (2)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'France', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00:01] They’re telling their story and their stories are more often than not pretty incredible and they show you photographs on their phone of their past life, and they are so proud of who they are and where they’ve come from. [00:00:17] They don’t want to be in Calle. They want to be home. [00:00:21] I have a small funny story where somebody at the very very beginning when we first arrived was trying to volunteer from the UK, was amazing, and he was trying to build a shelter with very minimum materials and a refugee had been watching him for two days silently from afar, respectfully, and after two days he came up and he said “please don’t be offended, and I hope you don’t mind, but can I help you because I’m a structural engineer in Syria and I built skyscrapers and I know that I can help you build this shelter better.”', 'Community;France;Third Person', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BA5NTrMA2dNf239sQgh3yjwAsCu1oIHh/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=114716866458378633429&rtpof=true&sd=true', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1tjEEs0KtHQEmBYwC4XSSKXP3wwzzSZaU/view?usp=sharing', 'Jess', NULL, 0, 0),
(254, '252', 'Danielle Lawrence (3)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'France', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00:01] They want to be remembered and treated as humans. And it’s very difficult when you are living in those conditions, in that situation with one change of clothes and very very minimal personal possessions, to come across in the way that you used to be at home or in the way you deserve and you know it’s very difficult for people to see past that when you meet people in Calle. [00:00:31] And its only by spending time and listening, a lot of listening to their stories respectfully and not judging that you then realise that you are actually very very lucky to be spending time with these people.', 'France;Third Person', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UYsQREOdogl9mfZwvrV7D9y4FaDR9K_p/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=114716866458378633429&rtpof=true&sd=true', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1IvjhZz6uxx6fc1Q7l10bnB6JxWL1TrpO/view?usp=sharing', 'Jess', NULL, 0, 0),
(255, '253', 'Nigel Farage (1)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Economic', NULL, 'France', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00-00:13] I travel through the Eurotunnel regularly I that’s that’s how I get to Brussels and Strasbourg for my work in the European Parliament there were times where I’ve been there when the lorries are are queueing for so long you can’t get the car in quickly. [00-13-00:20] I’ve been surrounded by scores of migrants running across the road, trying to get in the back door, all of that sort of thing, I found it fairly intimidating.[00-20-00:38] My impression, my feeling at Calais, is that things there are now virtually lawless, there have now been nine migrants killed this year trying to get through the tunnel. It seems to me, unless something radical is done, it’s only a matter of time before a British holiday maker or a British lorry driver gets killed there too.', 'Belgium;France;Politics,', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1WNuoRiIFD-9qd1lrsuaxcJNFaeD9AdQf/view?usp=sharing', 'Veronika', NULL, 0, 0),
(256, '254', 'Nigel Farage (2)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Economic', NULL, 'France', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00-00:25] There was a time, when it was the ferry port that attracted the big hordes, of migrants, but now, down by the ferry port, there are some very big strong secure fences, so their attention has shifted to Eurotunnel of course the weakness of Eurotunnel is that the SNCF, the French national railway line, obviously goes through there so you’ve only gotta go a mile or two further down the track to find fencing that is frankly pretty inadequate. [00:25-00:38] And I, I’m surprised that the French authorities haven’t done more to stop the situation. I sometimes get the impression they’d be quite pleased if everybody just got on the next train and disappeared off to Britain.', 'France;Politics', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1tjK8XPoy0aZgF-xrNKzl36UD_COcYLcI/view?usp=sharing', 'Veronika', NULL, 0, 0),
(257, '255', 'Nigel Farage (3)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', 'Economic', 'United Kingdom', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00] The intensity and the desperate effort of those who want to get to Britain, and we understand why they do, is becoming more and more severe\n[00:07] I just talked to the lorry drivers who, you know, are having bricks thrown in front of their tires, every attempt being made to actually stop the lorries so that people can try and get on\n[00:17] So the situation is bad', 'France;Politics;United Kingdom;', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FhBIzyo3_BVL0hyzGYLc11vVMfbco-wKIjdWxYsCNSE/edit?usp=sharing', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Fc0DrnzIURfhGCv-hGAG8m3jI6MBiP1u/view?usp=sharing', 'David', NULL, 0, 0),
(258, '256', 'Nigel Farage (4)', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Economic', 'United Kingdom', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00] Basically the european commission has said that anyone who lands in greece or in italy can stay\n[00:06] And it is because of that policy that we are seeing that massively increase pressure at Calais\n[ 00:11] I think the European Union needs to fundamentally rethink, frankly, what it’s doing [ 00:16] And why they are so desperate to get to britain, well firstly our economy, is performing far better than the Euro Zone\n[00:22] Secondly we have, regrettably, a big cash black market in this country\n[00:27] And thirdy, anyone who comes to britain illegally knows, that they are very unlikely to get caught, and if they are caught their chances of getting sent back is very very small\n[00:37] So we could actually, as a country, our government send out a message that says, anyone who comes to this country illegally via this route will not be allowed to stay.', 'France;Politics;United Kingdom', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LFqDjs42e5mrCn8gKjXRHJo9DFamJ6rmX_KWeyjzqX4/edit?usp=sharing', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1lew-QgvsBFSV4cIl_Yh-crU5O964vhpK/view?usp=sharing', 'David', NULL, 0, 0),
(261, '259', 'Hannah Rose Thomas', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', NULL, 'Syria', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00:0] The Kids, like their laughter, and the joy. Well one day, a couple of weeks ago in Jordan’s Zaatari camp, we got the wrong, we got hold of the wrong paint. [00:09:0] So It was permanent paint and we were all covered in this paint, like hands and feet and it wasn\'t coming off with water. And some girls had like, blue all the way up their hands.[00:18:0] We had to get white spirit to scrub ourselves and the girls were all laughing as they took my hands and feet and scrubbed me. They then splashed me with water at the end. And that was almost like the best part of it.[00:26:0] But even the painting you know, we just like, I just like, it’s just the, and yah, the love, I, i\'ve been changed more about my, by doing this project. More, than, I, I don’t,I don’t know exactly the full impact of a few days painting. [00:40:0] Hope to bring some joy, creative chaos, and some freedom. But I\'ve been changed by the love shown by these girls, but also the boys as well, they are just, their warmth and welcome. And having the language as well is extraordinarily help in bridging those barriers and just communicating. [00:59:0] And, I\'ve, it’s just, I\'ve absolutely, have been so deeply touched and changed by it.', 'Wellbeing;Third person', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pg5ie5nJ6uXGO1M1n0vMmzuZbVQmOcPr/view?usp=sharing', 'David', NULL, 0, 0),
(262, '260', 'Hannah Rose Thomas', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', NULL, 'Syria', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '[00:00:00] I was so deeply touched by some of them, what they, what they, said to me. [00:08:00] Their, some of the syrian women, in burqas, who got involved in the project. came up, actually one of them, one of the ladies was in tears, and she said um, you’re, you’re, transforming these tents, that, that umm, these children have been living in, and that they, our kids can not understand what it means. Why they are in these tenets, why they had to move away, really. [00:26:00] They can\'t understand that you’re bringing them hope again, it\'s so good to see them smile and she cried and, and I cried.', 'Wellbeing;Third person', '', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Dm9UzUpkXYtGr44S5ezTRuNyZL4g_FRy/view?usp=sharing', 'David', NULL, 0, 0),
(263, '261', 'Hassan Alli', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Germany;Hungary;Lebanon;Libia;Macodnia;Sudan;Syria', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '(0:00:01) My name is Hassan Alli, from Sudan, Darfur. \n(00:00:07) Me go to Libia, after go to Libia go to Syria, then go to Lebanon, work some 2 years, after come back to Syria then go to Turkish, go to Greece.  \n(00:00:30) after go to Macedonia, live Macedonia 2 years, after here I go Macedonia, go to Serbia, Hungary and Serbia, German and come here. \n(00:00:48) It’s a long time, then half chance go to England, maybe we go, maybe we die, you know everyday, everyday. ', 'assimilation;Germany;Hungary;Lebanon;Libia;Macodnia;Sudan;Syria;work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Sydney', NULL, 0, 0),
(264, '262', 'Ibrahim', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Child Migration', 'Education', NULL, 'England;Syria', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '(00:00:00) In Oxford, we started a small group called Oxford …. for Syria, pretty academic really, with all concentrated-on talks, raising awareness and telling people about the situation. \n(00:00:10) They were talking about the few hundred people stranded there, that did include Syrians, so I decided to make a trip. \n(00:00:18) There I was dealing with minors on the first trip, and it was such a shock, cause I have always heard about stories, you know there everywhere, on social media. \n(00:00:27) Then it became even more interesting, I met a few of the young ones, I met a eleven-year kid from Syria, I met a eight-year-old who had an uncle with him, that’s why he could not get through, most of his family is there, but because he had a accompany there he could not get through.  \n(00:00:46) But we are talking about an eight years child, whats the act that will give him ball and look at the smile on his face, his got his own ball now and he wants to find friends to play with, and hes just there this tiny little thing in the crap hole. ', 'Community;Ethnicity;Family;Syria;Thrid Person', '', NULL, NULL, 'Sydney', NULL, 0, 0),
(265, '263', 'Jess', NULL, NULL, 'Audio', 'Immigration', 'Education', NULL, NULL, 'England;France', 'CMBMN', NULL, NULL, '(00:00:00) My name is jess, I\'m here in Calais, working with a small charity called art refuge UK and we’re really small team of art psychotherapists and visual artist. \n(00:00:12) I am so embarrassed and ashamed at all that we can be doing in the UK and all that France can be doing, as two countries that are pretty sorted in this world. \n(00:00:28) I know that certain politicians and political party leaders are very quick to agree that refugees across the centuries have given us so much to the UK, the bank of England was built by seven refugees, the clock tower of big ben designed by refugees, fish and chips come from a Portuguese and other migrant population and I can’t believe that when we take so much from the be for the fact that the world is built on migration, we’re not able to support people in need. ', 'England;EU;Politics;Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, 'Sydney', NULL, 0, 0);
