(1661, '1659', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'The Escape Artists. This isn’t exactly true. I know we left Poland right before WWII, and escaped Ireland during the potato famine, AND we were originally French but escaped to Ireland (?) due to something historical that I have forgotten. My point is, we migrated a lot, within three generations, and now we are integrated. But we haven’t forgotten.', 'Culture;Family;third person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
