(1694, '1692', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Germany', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My mother’s father was a German Jewish refugee who escaped as a teen and arrived during start of WWII on a boat in Liverpool.\n', 'Genocide;Germany;Religion;Third person;War', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'taken for HMD', 0, 0),
(1695, '1693', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Australia', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My maternal grandparents, my mother and her siblings migrated from North Yorkshire in the late\n1960s to Australia. I have dual Australian/British citizenship through this connection. How is it so\neasy for me to claim this, and so difficult for others in the same situation, but from other countriescolonised by Britain?? Coverage of Britain’s colonial and imperial past, and its effects on migration, both to and from the UK, could answer this question. I’m back living in the UK now!!', 'Politics;third person', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(1696, '1694', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Gower is a French surname. Upon research my ancestors came over in 1066 after the Battle of\nHastings. My grandfather was a naval commander, my father was born and christened in Malta on a battleship despite being ‘British’.\n', 'third person; war', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
