(1904, '1902', '', NULL, '1930s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'No details', 'No details', 'Germany', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandparents, [names redacted] came from Germany in he late 1930s. Lilo was from a Jewish family escaping persecution, Henry was an activist fighting against the Nazis. They met in a German refugee cultural club in London, married, had kids, and stayed.', 'Ethnicity;Family;Genocide;Germany;Jewish;London;Thirdperson;War', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'LMA Event/taken for HMD names: Liselotte and Heinrich (Henry)', 0, 0),
(1905, '1903', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Education', NULL, NULL, 'Nigeria', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My Nigerian grandparents met at university in Brighton, got married in Trafalgar Square and returned to Nigeria. My parents met at uni in Nigeria, married here to work as doctors and are still here today, loyal to the NHS!', 'Brighton;Education;Ethnicity;Family;Healthcare;Nigeria;Nigerian', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'Launch Party', 0, 0),
(1906, '1904', NULL, NULL, '1950s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandmother moved here from Toronto in the mid 50s. Commonwealth migrants are left off a lot of narratives of post war immigration if they’re white – understandingly as the prejudice was much lower, but It’d be interesting to hear more of their stories and know why they came here too.', 'Empire;Family;Thirdperson;Toronto', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1907, '1905', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Trinidad', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'From what my grandma has told me, she travelled from Trinidad on the Windrush to the UK and settled here and worked as a nurse.', 'Assimilation;Family;Healthcare;Thirdperson;UK', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'the challenge', 0, 0),
(1908, '1906', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My granddad moved to the UK from Riga with his family (he was 1 of 9 children). Rumour has it that when they got off the boat, they thought they were in New York. They were actually in Barrow-in-Furness!', 'Barrow-in-Furness;Family;Riga;USA', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1909, '1907', 'George A. SLC', NULL, '1940s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Germany', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandmother immigrated here from Germany in 1948 after marrying a British officer. The story she always tells is her meeting Hitler in 1938 at a rally! So strange, a completely different world.', 'Family;Germany', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1910, '1908', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandfather was an Austrian-Polish Jew who narrowly missed imprisonment in a concentration camp. My grandma was born and raised in Shanghai until age 16, before coming to the UK>', 'Australian-Polish;Ethnicity;Family;Jew;Religion;Shanghai;UK', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1911, '1909', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Love', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandmother was exiled from her country at 18 because she fell in love with the ‘wrong’ person and had to start her life on her own in North London.', 'Alienation;Family;NorthLondon', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1912, '1910', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'china', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandad came to London by boat after the Japanese invasion on China, fell in love with my grandma and stayed.\n', 'China;Culture;Family;Japanese;London;War', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'The challenge', 0, 0),
(1913, '1911', 'Alyth', NULL, '1890s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Latvia, Poland', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My maternal grandparents came to Liverpool, escaping the pogroms against Jews from Latvia + Odessa and settled in Manchester in around 1890. My paternal grandparents came from Poland, escaping the pogroms, and settled in London.', 'Family, latvia, poland, Genocide', '', NULL, NULL, 'RL', 'taken for HMD', 0, 0),
(1914, '1912', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ireland', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandad came from Ireland as an orphan and became a politician in Rochester and met the Queen once!', 'Family;Ireland;Politics;Rochester', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'Britannia VPS', 0, 0),
(1915, '1913', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandmother migrated here from Cyprus to carry out an operation on her 10 yr. old son. It wasn’t possible in Cyprus. Her daughter met my dad, fell in love, and married.', 'Cyprus;Family;Healthcare', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1916, '1914', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Uganda', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandad was working in Uganda, but it became unsafe. He was brought to Britain my plane. He knew no one, had nothing, no family. Years later he found his family again.', 'Britain;Family;Uganda', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1917, '1915', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My great-grandfather came to Liverpool from Dublin. Their family name was McDonell, but they changed it to McDonald and pretended to be Scottish to get jobs! Everyone in Liverpool has some migrant ancestry – people don’t think of it as different.', 'Dublin;Ethnicity;Family;Liverpool;Scottish;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'Teach first summer project', 0, 0),
(1918, '1916', NULL, NULL, '1960s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'India;England', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandfather came to England in the early 1960s when there was a call for work. He left his village in Punjab (India), travelled to Bombay and then arrived in England. So thankful as this country has given s so many opportunities. XX', 'Bombay;England;Family;India;Punjab', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1919, '1917', NULL, NULL, '1950s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, 'Love', NULL, 'Ireland', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My granny moved here from Ireland in the 1950s when she was just 16! She had lots of interesting jobs including in a sausage factory! She fell in love and raised a family here.', 'Family;Ireland;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'South London Cares', 0, 0),
(1920, '1918', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Mauritius;UK', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandparents decided to travel to the UK for better work. They came from Mauritius.', 'Family;Mauritius;UK;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'The challange', 0, 0),
(1921, '1919', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Netherlands;UK', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'They were Jews who came over in the early wave of Jewish immigration to the UK – latest know was in the latter half of the 19th century (great-grandparents from the Netherlands). I have – strangely enough – treasured the felling of ‘not quite belonging’. Culture conflict is particularly good for children in my view, as it helps develop independent thinking.', 'Alienation;Assimilation;Culture;Ethnicity;Jews;Netherlands;UK', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'Launch Party', 0, 0),
(1922, '1920', NULL, NULL, '1940s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', NULL, NULL, 'Poland;Russia', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My great grandparents came over from Russia and Poland as a result of the pogroms against the Jew. They were an immigrant family in the East End of London in the 1940s. My grandfather watched Moseley’s brown shirts march down Cable Street. He was scare and realised his best chance of survival was assimilation. From that point he ditched a lot of his Jewish customs and Jewishness – changed his name and assimilated. He was a Brit first, then a Jew, but I think he felt Britain always treated him as a Jew.', 'Assimilation;Culture;Ethnicity;Jew;Poland;Russia;', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1923, '1921', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'Economic', 'No details', 'Australia;England', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'When my grandparents had my mum, they moved to Munich and then they moved to Australia for my grandpa’s work. After that, they moved to England.', 'Australia;England;Family;Munich;Work', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1924, '1922', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Australia', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My cousin Joan emigrated to Australia under the 10-pound scheme. She enjoyed the life and married Alan, a Scotsman, in Australia. She came to the UK once, but all the family missed her over the years, and were not able to go to see her.', 'Australia;Ethnicity;Family;Scotsman;UK', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1925, '1923', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My DNA shows I am 82% English, 7% Spanish, 6% Finnish, 5% Irish, Scot, Welsh, 1% Nigerian. History of my surname suggests we came from Normandy with William the Conqueror, but no sign of that in DNA.', 'Culture;Ethnicity;Englsih;Finnish;Irish;Nigerian;Normandy;Welsh', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1926, '1924', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I left with the intention of never coming back. I found my home in Los Angeles Hermosa Beach. Unfortunately, I had to return to London and still now I miss the sunshine and the happy beach life.', 'London;Los Angeles', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1927, '1925', NULL, NULL, '1940s', 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Germany', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Margott my mum came over from Germany in 1945 age 21. Met my dad Leslie, English. Married, became an English citizen and did not stay fir 6 months, stayed till she was 87!', 'English;Ethnicity;Family;Germany', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1928, '1926', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Economic', 'Education', NULL, 'England;Ireland', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Both my parents’ families migrated from Ireland to England for my grandfather’s work. My mother enjoyed life in the North until she moved back at 14. My dad went to uni in Scotland, worked in England and they both live in N. Ireland now.', 'Education;England;Family;Ireland;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', 'SLC', 0, 0),
(1929, '1927', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Canada', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'At the beginning of the war a few of my Nan’s family chose to be shipped over to Canada and never returned. They have visited a few times, however I have never met them.', 'Canada;War', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1930, '1928', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'England', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My parents left the UK before I was born and brought up my brother and me overseas, but made sure we visited our grandparents in England as often as possible. I didn’t think until today how blessed I am to have roots in a country where I feel free and safe.', 'England;Family;Third person;Work', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1931, '1929', '', NULL, '1930s', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My great grandfather arrived in the UK in the 1930\'s, but we don’t know where from, as he kept it a secret for his whole life!', 'Third Person', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'SLC', 0, 0),
(1932, '1930', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My great grandfather was brought over as a slave. My grandmother married a white Irish man. My dad and mum are white British. Apparently, I am white British.', 'Ethnicity; Ireland; Race; Third Person', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1933, '1931', 'Monique', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Congo', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My name (is) Monique. I come from Congo in Africa. I leave UK 2071. I am happy to live UK because UK is very nice. My family live in Congo.\r\n', 'Africa;Congo;Family', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Alyth', 0, 0),
(1934, '1932', '', NULL, '1650s', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Barbados', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I am the first generation to be born in the UK since my family left to live in Barbados in 1650. The family were Quakers. Most families that were planters were also owners of boats and therefore captains and could perform marriages. Most early settlers formed local governments so they were ministers, most held a position in the army so were captain, Lt. General. It sounds grand but probably it was not.', 'Barbados; Culture; Empire; Family Race; Religion; ', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1935, '1933', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'As I looked around, I realised that I’m the one left here with my mum! Her sisters and my brother all in other countries – 21 in Australia – I can’t get there because I cant get the points – ridiculous.', 'Australia; Family; Third Person', '', NULL, NULL, 'PKY', NULL, 0, 0),
(1936, '1934', 'Mark', NULL, '1960s', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Economic', 'No details', 'No details', 'Canada', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My parents both emigrated from here from Scotland and Wales to Canada (1967), for the opportunity. But I came back! ', 'Canada; Family: Third Person; Wales', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1937, '1935', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'England;Pakistan', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My mum’s brother came from Pakistan to England to get a better job and he wanted to live in England.', 'England;Family;Pakistan;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1938, '1936', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Canada', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Canada. Mother moved with grandparents who previously moved from Eastern Europe, who previously moved from somewhere else.', 'Canada;Eastern Europe;Family', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1939, '1937', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Economic', 'No details', 'No details', 'Australia;Netherlands;Sweden', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My auntie, uncle and cousin migrated from Holland to Australia because of work. They still live there now. They studied there and my oldest cousin completed her master’s in Sweden.', 'Australia;Family;Netherlands;Sweden;Third person;Work', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1940, '1938', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Love', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I moved to London four years ago for ‘love’, crossing the Channel with no ship but with hopes!! Love evolved, but my love for this beautiful and welcoming country begun.', 'London;Love', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1941, '1939', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Abu Dhabi;USA', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My dad moved to America when he was young with my uncle and grandparents, and then moved back to the UK. Also, my cousins moved to Abu Dhabi a few years ago for work and recently came back.', 'Abu Dhabi;Family;Third Person;USA;', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1942, '1940', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Nigeria', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I have an uncle that came from Nigeria and came to London.', 'London;Nigeria', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'uncle called Abe ', 0, 0),
(1943, '1941', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Part 2 – My grandfather brought my mother and my grandmother. My mother had an arranged marriage to my father, and the rest is history!', 'Family', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1944, '1942', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Trinidad and Tobago', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My mum and her family grew up in Trinidad. We have no family connection to Trinidad and Tobago, but it is in our hearts. We return most years and eat Trinidadian food very often. I feel more comfortable there than in the UK.', 'Culture;Family;Food;Trinidad and Tobago;Trinidadian', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1945, '1943', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'I have thought I could be a migrant, because moving around Europe does not mean ‘migration’. Since 2016, I am a migrant and still European.', 'Culture;Europe;European', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1946, '1944', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My childhood was spent in English brick houses when visiting my cousins outside of London. Now they have moved on to another country, and I live in an English brick house instead.', 'London', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1947, '1945', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'No details', 'No details', 'Poland;Russia', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'Most of my great grandparents came to Britain in the late 19th century from Poland or Russia for a better life. They were lucky to be treated well and far better than in Poland and Russia. We should, as a country, be able to take in people who want to make a new life here.', 'Britain;Family;Poland;Russia', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1948, '1946', 'Robert', NULL, '1920s', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Austria;Ireland;Poland;UK;Ukraine;USA', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My grandfather came to the US from Britain in the 1920\'s when he was a teenager. His father had come to Hackney from Austria. My family in the US has roots in Poland, Ukraine, Ireland and the UK. They are who I am.', 'Austria;Britain;Family;Ireland;Poland;Third Person;UK;Ukraine;USA', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1949, '1947', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Education', NULL, NULL, 'Iran;Uk', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My fiance’s sister’s husband was born in Tehran, Iran. After studying in the UK under TIER 4, then working under TIER 2, he has now naturalised as a British citizen and lives in Bristol.', 'Education;Family;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Anandu Shabu', NULL, 0, 0),
(1950, '1948', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', 'No details', 'No details', '', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My great grandfather came as a slave. He translated Yoruba.', 'Empire;Family;Language;Youruba', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1951, '1949', 'Tess', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Love', 'No details', 'No details', 'Austria;Engloand;USA', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My great aunt emigrated to the USA to marry my great uncle. My aunt emigrated from Australia to England.', 'Australia;England;Usa', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1952, '1950', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Emigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Mauritius', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My mum moved to the UK from Mauritius. My mum loves the weather.\r\n', 'Family;Mauritius;Uk', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1953, '1951', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', 'Forced Migration/Enslavement', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Netherlands', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My family came to London from the Netherlands pre WW2 as economic migrants. It’s just as well that they did because we are Jews. All the family who stayed in the Netherlands were murdered in the Holocaust. Never again.', 'Family;Netherlands;war;poltiics;genocide', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'taken for HMD', 0, 0),
(1954, '1952', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Emigration', 'Love', NULL, NULL, 'Bangladesh', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My auntie moved from England to Bangladesh because her husband lived there, so she had to go back.', 'Family;Bangladesh;third person;friends', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1955, '1953', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Love', 'Child Migration', 'No details', 'Syria', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My great grandad was adopted by Syrian people. He met my great grandma and they sent my grandma to Britain and then my grandad to get married and had my mum.', 'Family;Syria;friends;third person', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1956, '1954', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', 'No details', 'No details', 'Philippines', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'No one in my family emigrated from here, but both my parents migrated from Philippines to Austria in hopes for a better life there. My mum didn’t have a job at first, she didn’t even have place to sleep when she met the sister of my dad in a tram. She offered her shelter. In the same apartment lived my dad. That’s how they met. Both of them worked really hard to give me and my older sister a happy life.', 'Family;Philippines;third person;Austria;work', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1957, '1955', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Wales', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My ancestors are Huguenots – I came from Wales to London and fell in love with the East End. Others moved to Australia, the US and back to France.', 'Family;USA;Australia;France;Wales', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Launch party', 0, 0),
(1958, '1956', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Love', NULL, NULL, 'Dundee', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My girlfriend is from Dundee!', 'Family;dundee;friends;third person', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1959, '1957', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Domenica', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My granny came from Domenica.', 'Family;Domenica;third person', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1960, '1958', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Phlippines', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My mum, dad and brother emigrated here from Philippines, Manila, before I was born.', 'Family;Philippines;third person;Austria;work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', 'Marvin THA 2017', 0, 0),
(1961, '1959', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Ireland ', 'Disc', 'Someone in my family emigrated from here', NULL, 'My parents moved from the UK to Ireland in the 1980\'s. Me and my 2 siblings moved back to Britain a few years ago. I am so grateful I’ve been able to move freely between these countries and how the British people will open their minds to migrants and recognise they too are migrants.', 'Family;Ireland;assimilation;wellbeing;third person', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1962, '1960', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Ghana;Italy', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My friends migrated from Italy because his parents were from Ghana. They then moved to England because he thought he could make friends.', 'Family;Ghana;Italy;third person;friends', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1963, '1961', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'USA', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'Amelia was born in England then left to go to America.', 'USA', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1964, '1962', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Trinidad', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My parents and family never migrated, there is something similar to migration. My mom moved to the UK, so did my family. They are trying to stay but in the week my nana got sent back on a plane back to Trinidad.', 'Family;Trinidad;UK', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1965, '1963', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Czech Republic', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'I’m a modern gypsy nomadic girl living out of her suitcase. I’d not say I’m a migrant, at least from the point of permanently being in the UK, although I live in London on and off since 2012. I’m a model from Czech Republic, that’s maybe why I travel and move a lot.', 'Family;Czech Republic;work', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1966, '1964', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Spain', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'I would like to live in Spain because it is sunny.', 'Family;Spain;wellbeing', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1967, '1965', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Love', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My aunt moved here because her love lived here but soon he passed on so my mum moved here to comfort her. My dad soon moved here in the UK and met her. They then had 3 kids. It’s my mum’s birthday today.', 'Family;third person;friends', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1968, '1966', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Scotland', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My great grandparents moved from Scotland to the East end of London and we’ve lived near London ever since. I’d like to find out more about my heritage on my mum’s side. I think migration and mixing up cultures is so important to building and more understanding nation – and to finding new delicious foods!', 'Family;third person;Scotland;assimilation', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1969, '1967', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Nigeria', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'My family are all from Nigeria and I have British nationality.', 'Family;Nigeria;third person;assimilation', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1970, '1968', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'China;Australia', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'I believe you can encourage but my parents (white British) were born in China and Australia and travelled. We didn’t settle in the UK until I was 11 years old so I don’t feel rooted anywhere. Rosalind', 'Family;China;Australia;alienation', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1971, '1969', '', NULL, '', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'No details', 'No details', 'No details', 'Germany', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'I don’t know much about anyone past my great grandparents, but I am aware of a family crest that hung on my childhood home of a Lord Beresford from Ireland. Also a German link from aunt’s family tree. My great aunt worked on a family tree, but where is it?', 'Family;Germany;Ireland;third person', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
(1972, '1970', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hull', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'I was born in Hull, there isn’t much diversity there, but moving to London a year ago has made me embrace different backgrounds and upbringings.', 'Family;culture;Hull', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
(1973, '1971', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Germany;Caribbean;Nigeria', 'Disc', 'No known migrants in my family', NULL, 'Or at least, when tracing back my family tree. But my niece and nephew in London have a Nigerian grandfather, my other nieces had a German grandmother, and my foster brother’s parents were Caribbean.', 'Family;Nigeria;Germany;Caribbean', '', NULL, NULL, 'Zuza', NULL, 0, 0),
