(2678, '2673', '', NULL, '1940s', 'Image', 'No details', 'Economic', 'Education', 'No details', 'India;Germany;Canada', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My nationalities: British and Canadian. Ethnicity: Punjabi, Sikh. Countries lived in: UK, Germany, Canada. Cities lived in: Birmingham, Blackburn, Cambridge, Heidelberg, London, Vancouver. Jobs: Derivatives Trader, University Professor.  My parents were born in Punjab, India in the 1940s. They moved to Kenya and then came to Britain in the early 1960s. I was born in Birmingham in the 70s. When still a child we moved to Blackburn, Lancashire, which was a shock for me. The north is almost another country! I moved down south to study. I enjoyed university so much, I ended up doing a PHD, moved to Canada to work as a professor. While there, I got married to an Italian and had 2 kids. She wanted to move to London, so here we are! I enjoy being back home. It\'s easier to live in a familiar place! Life must be tough for immigrants.', 'India;UK;Germany;Canada;Commerce;Education;Family;Race;Ethnicity;Celebration;Pride', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0),
