(6162, '6154', 'Andy', NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Poland;Baltic states;Russia;India', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'My mother Benigna was born in the Baltic states – though she always used to say she came from Poland. She was taken to Russia during the war. She made her way to England after the war via India with her sisters and mother, arriving aged 13. She trained as a nurse and met my dad and that’s why I’m here! She used to sound super-English on the phone! Andy, Guildford', 'Family;War', '', NULL, NULL, 'Lauren', NULL, 0, 0),
(6164, '6156', NULL, NULL, '1970s', 'Image', 'Immigration', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kenya;India', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'Following my dear grandfathers death my family had two options, leave Kenya to their native India or embark on a journey to britain. of the two the first was an easier option but the second had far better prospects. A widowed woman took a brave decision in 1973 and now in 2015 she has over 30 proud british decendents who form an essential backbone of this country. thank you britain xxxx', 'Family', '', NULL, NULL, 'Lauren', NULL, 0, 0),
