(6765, '6757', NULL, NULL, '1930s;1940s', 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Refugee/Asylum', 'Child Migration', NULL, 'Germany', 'Disc', 'At least one of my grandparents migrated here', NULL, 'My grandma arrived in Britain on one of the last Kinder Transport to leave Germany - she was Jewish so her parents sent her away to save her life. She had a high fever when she arrived in the UK, so the immigration authority should have sent her back but they didn\'t! Her father died in a concentration camp, and after the war she threw away all his letters and her diary - she didn\'t keep much of German culture and she didn’t teach her children German but she always remembered her mother making apple strudel and swearing in Polish.', 'Culture;Ethnicity;Europe;Family;Food;Genocide;Germany;Language;Poland;Politics;Race;Racism;Religion;Third Person;Wellbeing;War', '', NULL, NULL, 'Alice Di Tella', NULL, 1, 0),
