(7025, '7017', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Image', 'Immigration', 'Economic', NULL, NULL, 'Philippines', 'Disc', 'At least one of my parents migrated here', NULL, 'After having a child, my older sister [and] my parents moved to the UK, presumably for work as the opportunities in the Philippines are more limited compared to the UK. Me and my brother were born in England. Because of this, I couldn’t really understand Filipino culture or even their language. Therefore, I felt like I didn’t really belong with the other Filipinos at gatherings, which is kind of the opposite of how my parents or my sister would have felt. For example, the way I speak is very different to my ancestors and my family friends, and doing greetings is kind of awkward too. Over the past years though, I’ve grown to be in touch [with] my original roots and learn to call the Philippines and England my home.', 'Alienation;Assimilation;Asia;Celebration;Community;Culture;Ethnicity;Family;Friends;Language;Philippines;Third Person;Work', '', NULL, NULL, 'Alice Di Tella', NULL, 0, 0),
